article.headline: San Diego 82, San Diego Christian 48
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Chris Lewis scored a career-high 19 points and Roberto Mafra added 13 to lead San Diego to an 82-48 win over San Diego Christian on Saturday. Lewis, starting for the second time this season, was 7-for-11 from the floor, including 3-for-4 from 3-point range. Lewis also led all players with seven rebounds. San Diego (3-3), coming off consecutive double-digit losses to No. 25 Wisconsin and 22nd-ranked Miami, shot 58.8 percent from the field against its NAIA opponent. James Green led San Diego Christian (2-3) with 10 points and Craig Jackson added nine. Brandon Johnson scored 10 points and had seven assists off the bench for the Toreros, who took the lead for good at 9-8. San Diego held the Eagles to only 38 percent shooting from the field and held a 36-21 edge in rebounding.
